Here is a basic CSS script that you can use as a starting point:

```
<style>
/* Add your CSS declarations within the <style> tags */
body {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  font-size: 16px;
  color: #333;
  line-height: 1.5;
}

h1 {
  font-size: 36px;
  color: #007bff;
  text-align: center;
  margin-top: 50px;
}

p {
  margin: 0;
}

a {
  color: #007bff;
  text-decoration: none;
}

a:hover {
  text-decoration: underline;
}

/* Add more CSS declarations as needed */
</style>
```

In this CSS script, we've defined some basic styles for the body, headings (`<h1>`), paragraphs (`<p>`), and links (`<a>`). You can modify these styles to fit your specific needs. 

It's important to include this code within the `<head>` of your HTML document, for example:

```
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>My CSS Sample</title>

  <style>
  /* Add your CSS code here */
  </style>

</head>
<body>

<!-- Your HTML content here -->

</body>
</html>
```

I hope this helps!

Sure! Here's an example CSS script that you can use to add information in center-right:

```
<style>
.center-right {
  position: fixed;
  top: 50%;
  right: 0;
  transform: translateY(-50%);
  width: 25%;
  text-align: center;
  background-color: #fff;
  padding: 20px;
  border: 1px solid #ccc;
  border-radius: 5px;
  box-shadow: 0 2px 5px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
}

.center-right h2 {
  font-size: 24px;
  color: #333;
  margin-top: 0;
}

.center-right p {
  font-size: 16px;
  color: #666;
  margin-bottom: 0;
}
</style>
```

In this code, we define a `<div>` with the class `center-right` and use CSS to position it in the center-right of the screen. 

The `position: fixed;` property fixes the position of the div on the screen, so it won't scroll along with the rest of the page. The `top: 50%;` and `transform: translateY(-50%);` properties center the div vertically, while `right: 0;` places it at the right side of the screen. 

We also give the div a `width` of 25% to control its size, and apply some styles for the text content inside the div, including a heading and some paragraphs.

You can customize this CSS as needed, and use the class `center-right` on your desired HTML element to apply these styles.
